    {
        "id": 2155217868,
        "number": 234,
        "title": "Observation on Banking-System : It Cannot Register New User from Registration Interface/Page",
        "state": "closed",
        "created_at": "2024-02-26T21:46:35Z",
        "updated_at": "2024-05-02T10:46:42Z",
        "closed_at": "2024-05-02T10:46:42Z",
        "author": "eteimopius",
        "comments": 3,
        "labels": [],
        "assignees": [],
        "locked": false,
        "body": "I would like to thank the Author of the Banking System for the wonderful and highly educative work done on the project.\r\n\r\nHowever, I observed that one is unable to register a new user into the database \"AspNetUser Table' using the Register.html interface/page. The system successfully login with the initial seeded data but one cannot register a new user into the database.\r\n\r\nThus, Recaptcha Secret keys were added to the AppSettings Json file, and ConfirmEmail was also disabled on  StartUp.cs file but it could not resolve the inability to register a new user.\r\n\r\nIt would be appreciated if you could give further steps one could explore in resolving the problem.\r\n\r\nThanks immensely\r\n\r\n",
        "url": "https://github.com/banksystembg/BankSystem/issues/234"
    },
    {
        "id": 933636930,
        "number": 230,
        "title": "Transaction boundary issue in InternalController.Create()",
        "state": "open",
        "created_at": "2021-06-30T12:07:27Z",
        "updated_at": "2021-08-08T12:59:05Z",
        "closed_at": null,
        "author": "ayende",
        "comments": 3,
        "labels": [
            "High priority"
        ],
        "assignees": [],
        "locked": false,
        "body": "See here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/banksystembg/BankSystem/blob/master/src/Web/BankSystem.Web/Areas/MoneyTransfers/Controllers/InternalController.cs#L97-L127\r\n\r\nYou have two calls to `CreateMoneyTransferAsync()`, one to withdraw the money and the other to deposit it. \r\nHowever, they are done as two separate database transactions, which means that you have the option of partial transaction.",
        "url": "https://github.com/banksystembg/BankSystem/issues/230"
